00:13:07.630 --> 00:13:09.400
So what's the physics here?

00:13:09.400 --> 00:13:11.660
Surfaces are high-energy
regions.

00:13:11.660 --> 00:13:12.410
Why?

00:13:12.410 --> 00:13:16.020
Because when you're inside
the crystal, you have the

00:13:16.020 --> 00:13:18.250
prescribed number of
nearest neighbors.

00:13:18.250 --> 00:13:19.950
Let's say you're in
an FCC crystal.

00:13:19.950 --> 00:13:21.350
You're an aluminum atom.

00:13:21.350 --> 00:13:23.560
So you're an aluminum atom
and you've got 12 nearest

00:13:23.560 --> 00:13:26.180
neighbors because you're
FCC, except if

00:13:26.180 --> 00:13:27.410
you're at the free surface.

00:13:27.410 --> 00:13:29.810
If you're an aluminum atom at
the free surface you don't

00:13:29.810 --> 00:13:30.920
have 12 nearest neighbors.

00:13:30.920 --> 00:13:33.770
Because if I look down I've got
aluminum atoms all over.

00:13:33.770 --> 00:13:36.130
If I look up, I've
got nothing.

00:13:36.130 --> 00:13:38.740
So axiomatically, I've got a
different number of bonds.

00:13:38.740 --> 00:13:39.775
Why do we form bonds?

00:13:39.775 --> 00:13:42.240
We form bonds in order
to lower the

00:13:42.240 --> 00:13:43.480
energy of the system.

00:13:43.480 --> 00:13:46.850
But axiomatically, the ones at
the top can't form the same

00:13:46.850 --> 00:13:48.530
number of bonds, so they
are not in the

00:13:48.530 --> 00:13:50.820
same low energy state.

00:13:50.820 --> 00:13:55.520
So once you get the connection
between lower number of bonds,

00:13:55.520 --> 00:13:59.590
higher energy state, then any
place, free surface, internal

00:13:59.590 --> 00:14:04.010
surface, is going to be
relatively high energy.

00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:15.570
Relatively higher energy than
atoms in the matrix.

00:14:15.570 --> 00:14:16.080
Matrix.

00:14:16.080 --> 00:14:17.060
